recordings.rmk:
Two clips appended, beginning and ending "clicks" removed from each.  Noise reduction and normalization applied in Audacity. There is highway noise at one point but not edited out as the birds calls were intense and distinctive at that point.

Four birds were involved in territorial dispute at location of previous year nest site.  Pair first observed in that location this year on 3/3 and 3/4/2020.  Interaction became most intense when the birds were closest to the stand of mature pines where a pair nested successfully last year.  Much diving/swooping and aggressive vocalizations took place as the birds neared that spot.

Location is a small stand of mature pines at the edge of a mixed cypress/hardwood swamp and planted pine plantation of about 3 years maturity.

recordings.rmk:
Recorded using Nokia Lumia 635 with Audio Recorder HiFi app; edited with Audacity: high-pass filter and volume amplification.

Four STKIs in flight overhead.  They began circling my position, calling repeatedly.  I assume I was near a potential nesting site, though I could not locate any such nest in the vicinity.  Note at the end of the track there is a alarm shriek from a White-tailed Deer which stumbled into this patch of forest and was startled by my presence.

Clear skies, light wind from the south, 28°C
